  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Institutional Visit to Canada by Chinmaya Organization for Rural Development (India)</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">Passage au Canada de la directrice de la Chinmaya Organization for Rural Development en Inde</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Chinmaya Organization for Rural Development (CORD) is a nongovernmental organization that seeks to empower women by increasing their ability to contribute to their families&apos; support and encouraging them to take on local leadership roles. This grant will allow Dr Kshama Metre, a practicing pediatrician and National Director of CORD (India), to visit Canada along with two individuals who have benefited from the organization&apos;s work in Kangra District, Himachal Pradesh, one of the most depressed states in India. The visit will include a presentation by Dr Metre as well as a workshop on Kangra-style painting illustrating the CORD approach to development. The overall goal of the visit is to demonstrate that well-managed foreign assistance at the local level can lead to self-sufficiency and improved livelihoods.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">La Chinmaya Organization for Rural Development (CORD) est une organisation non gouvernementale qui travaille &#xE0; l&apos;autonomisation des femmes en renfor&#xE7;ant leur capacit&#xE9; &#xE0; contribuer au soutien familial et en les encourageant &#xE0; exercer un leadership dans leur collectivit&#xE9;. Cette subvention permettra &#xE0; la dirigeante de CORD en Inde, la p&#xE9;diatre Kshama Metre, de se rendre au Canada en compagnie de deux personnes qui ont b&#xE9;n&#xE9;fici&#xE9; de l&apos;action de l&apos;organisme. Ces personnes sont du district de Kangra, qui se trouve dans l&apos;&#xC9;tat de l&apos;Himachal Pradesh, l&apos;un des plus pauvres de l&apos;Inde. La Dre Metre livrera un expos&#xE9;, et il y aura un atelier sur la peinture dans le style de Ka?gra qui permettra d&apos;illustrer l&apos;approche de CORD en mati&#xE8;re de d&#xE9;veloppement. La vis&#xE9;e globale de la visite est de d&#xE9;montrer que, g&#xE9;r&#xE9;e ad&#xE9;quatement &#xE0; l&apos;&#xE9;chelle locale, l&apos;aide &#xE9;trang&#xE8;re peut favoriser l&apos;autosuffisance et am&#xE9;liorer les moyens de subsistance.</narrative>
  </description>
